<p class="h2">Permissions for Written Works</p>
<p class="fl">Some of the articles in this dictionary have been adapted from other works published by Tyndale House Publishers, particularly <span class="ital">The Origin of the Bible</span> and <span class="ital">Who’s Who in Christian History.</span> In preparing several other articles, the editor, Philip Comfort, made some adaptions from his own previously published works, now no longer in print. These works are as follows: <span class="ital">New Commentary on the Whole Bible</span> (New Testament volume); <span class="ital">I Am the Way; Opening the Gospel of John</span> (with W. Hawley); <span class="ital">The Complete Guide to Bible Versions; The Quest for the Original Text of the New Testament; Early Manuscripts and Modern Translations of the New Testament;</span> and <span class="ital">The Inspired Word.</span></p>
